net.sf.saxon.value

Interface AnyExternalObject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GroundedValue, Item, Sequence
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Bindery.FailureValue, ObjectValue, Tuple

    public interface AnyExternalObject
extends Item
    An external object is a fourth kind of Item (after nodes, atomic values, and functions): it acts as a wrapper for a Java object (or, in C#, a .NET object).

    This interface deliberately does not use generics, enabling it to be used in the same way both in Java and C#.
